From: AsteroidOS Build System <build@asteroidos.org>
Date: Mon, 1 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add unnamespaced AsteroidApp alias for cmake compatibility

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [OE-specific workaround]

Apps such as asteroid-flashlight and asteroid-stopwatch use
  target_link_libraries(... AsteroidApp)
but the installed cmake export only defines the namespaced target
Asteroid::AsteroidApp.  CMake therefore treats "AsteroidApp" as a
plain library name (-lAsteroidApp) and never propagates
INTERFACE_INCLUDE_DIRECTORIES, so the compiler cannot find
<asteroidapp.h>.

Add an unnamespaced ALIAS target so both spellings resolve to the
same imported target and include-directory propagation works.
---
 src/app/AsteroidAppConfig.cmake.in | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/app/AsteroidAppConfig.cmake.in b/src/app/AsteroidAppConfig.cmake.in
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/src/app/AsteroidAppConfig.cmake.in
+++ b/src/app/AsteroidAppConfig.cmake.in
@@ -8,3 +8,9 @@ set(ASTEROID_MODULE_PATH "@PACKAGE_ASTEROID_MODULES_INSTALL_DIR@")
 
 include("${CMAKE_CURRENT_LIST_DIR}/AsteroidAppTargets.cmake")
 @PACKAGE_INCLUDE_QCHTARGETS@
+
+# Provide an unnamespaced alias so apps that link against "AsteroidApp"
+# (without the Asteroid:: namespace) still get the correct imported target.
+if(TARGET Asteroid::AsteroidApp AND NOT TARGET AsteroidApp)
+  add_library(AsteroidApp ALIAS Asteroid::AsteroidApp)
+endif()
